
[1]thallite

   THAL'LITE, n. [Gr. a green twig.] In mineralogy, a substance variously
   denominated by different authors. It is the epidote of Hauy,the
   delphinite of Saussure,and the pistacite of Werner. It occurs both
   crystallized and in masses.
